import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Miles_per_Gallon'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Miles_per_Gallon', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Cylinders'] = data['Cylinders'].astype(str)
    chart = sns.countplot(x='Cylinders', data=data)
    chart.set(title='What is the distribution of Cylinders?')
    for p in chart.patches:
        chart.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.0f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
